ocial security receipt and government, community and charitable support. This book sets out all that is wrong with the status quo, while also offering a powerful agenda for change. Also see ‘COVID-19 Collaborations: Researching Poverty and Low-Income Family Life during the Pandemic’ (Open Access) to find out more about the challenges of carrying out research during COVID-19.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCOVID-19 Pandemic, 2020-xEconomic aspectszGreat Britain. 0aEqualityzGreat Britain. 0aPoor familieszGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aGarthwaite, Kayleigh, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGarthwaite, Kayleigh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaufman, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPage, Geoff, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPage, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatrick, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPower, Maddy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPower, Maddy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPybus, Katie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPybus, Katie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311119677040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447364719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447364719/original  a978-3-11-119677-0  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles